          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Expresses the sense of the House of Representatives that the President is required to: (1) seek congressional authorization prior to any engagement of the U.S. Armed Forces against Syria, Iran, or Russia; and (2) consult with Congress before introducing the U.S. Armed Forces into situations of hostilities.</p> <p>Expresses the sense of the House that the use of the U.S. Armed Forces without congressional authorization is illegal and unconstitutional. <br /></p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2018-09-13T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
